---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'quick-verdict', text: 'Quick Verdict', level: 2 },
  { id: 'comparison-table', text: 'Side-by-Side Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'safetywing', text: 'SafetyWing', level: 2 },
  { id: 'allianz-care', text: 'Allianz Care', level: 2 },
  { id: 'img-global', text: 'IMG Global', level: 2 },
  { id: 'pricing', text: 'Pricing Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'long-stay-needs', text: 'What Long-Stay Travelers Need', level: 2 },
  { id: 'best-for', text: 'Which Is Best For You?', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'FAQs', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'SafetyWing Review', href: '/providers/safetywing' },
  { title: 'Allianz Care Review', href: '/providers/allianz-care' },
  { title: 'IMG Global Review', href: '/providers/img-global' },
  { title: 'Travel vs Expat Insurance', href: '/guides/travel-insurance-vs-expat-insurance' },
  { title: 'Snowbird Insurance', href: '/insurance-for/snowbirds' },
];

const mainComparisonColumns = [
  { key: 'feature', header: 'Feature' },
  { key: 'safetywing', header: 'SafetyWing' },
  { key: 'allianz', header: 'Allianz Care' },
  { key: 'img', header: 'IMG Global' },
];

const mainComparisonRows = [
  { feature: 'Insurance Type', safetywing: 'Travel medical', allianz: 'Health insurance', img: 'Health insurance' },
  { feature: 'Coverage Limit', safetywing: '$250,000', allianz: '€1M - €3M', img: '$1M - $8M' },
  { feature: 'Duration Limit', safetywing: 'Unlimited', allianz: 'Annual', img: 'Up to 2 years' },
  { feature: 'Routine Care', safetywing: 'Limited', allianz: 'Full', img: 'Full' },
  { feature: 'Pre-existing', safetywing: 'Not covered', allianz: 'Underwritten', img: 'Underwritten' },
  { feature: 'Home Visits', safetywing: '30 days/90', allianz: 'Optional add-on', img: 'Optional' },
  { feature: 'Flexibility', safetywing: 'Monthly', allianz: 'Annual', img: '6-24 months' },
  { feature: 'Best For', safetywing: 'Budget/flexible', allianz: 'Comprehensive', img: 'Mid-range' },
];

const pricingColumns = [
  { key: 'duration', header: 'Duration' },
  { key: 'safetywing', header: 'SafetyWing' },
  { key: 'allianz', header: 'Allianz Care' },
  { key: 'img', header: 'IMG Global' },
];

const pricingRows = [
  { duration: '3 Months, Age 35', safetywing: '$165-200', allianz: '$450-650', img: '$350-500' },
  { duration: '6 Months, Age 35', safetywing: '$330-400', allianz: '$900-1,300', img: '$650-900' },
  { duration: '12 Months, Age 35', safetywing: '$660-800', allianz: '$1,800-2,600', img: '$1,200-1,700' },
  { duration: '12 Months, Age 50', safetywing: '$1,000-1,200', allianz: '$3,000-4,500', img: '$2,000-3,000' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="SafetyWing vs Allianz vs IMG: Best Long-Stay Travel Insurance 2026"
  description="Compare insurance for extended trips and long stays abroad: SafetyWing, Allianz Care, and IMG Global. From gap years to snowbirds—coverage for 3+ months abroad."
  headline="SafetyWing vs Allianz vs IMG: Long-Stay Coverage Compared"
  subheadline="Staying abroad for 3-12 months? Three options from budget travel medical to comprehensive health insurance for extended stays."
  heroImage="/images/pages/provider-card-generic.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get Quotes"
  ctaButtonHref="/get-quotes"
>
  <h2 id="quick-verdict">Quick Verdict</h2>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 my-6">
    <div class="bg-amber-50 border-2 border-amber-300 rounded-lg p-5">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-amber-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Budget Choice</p>
      <p class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-2">SafetyWing</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-3">$55/mo. Monthly flexibility. Emergency coverage only. Best for young, healthy travelers.</p>
      <a href="/go/safetywing" class="inline-block w-full text-center bg-amber-600 hover:bg-amber-700 text-white text-sm font-medium py-2 px-4 rounded transition-colors no-underline" style="color: white !important;">Get SafetyWing Quote</a>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-green-50 border-2 border-green-300 rounded-lg p-5">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-green-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Best Coverage</p>
      <p class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Allianz Care</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-3">Real health insurance. Full routine care. Pre-existing conditions considered. Best for serious stays.</p>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block w-full text-center bg-green-600 hover:bg-green-700 text-white text-sm font-medium py-2 px-4 rounded transition-colors no-underline" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-neutral-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Middle Ground</p>
      <p class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-2">IMG Global</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-3">Health insurance at moderate cost. Good for 6-24 month stays. Solid all-around option.</p>
      <a href="/go/img-global" class="inline-block w-full text-center bg-neutral-700 hover:bg-neutral-800 text-white text-sm font-medium py-2 px-4 rounded transition-colors no-underline" style="color: white !important;">Get IMG Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p>
    Long stays (3-12+ months) fall between travel and expat insurance. SafetyWing is cheapest but provides emergency coverage only. Allianz offers real health insurance with full benefits. IMG bridges the gap with solid coverage at mid-range prices.
  </p>

  <h2 id="comparison-table">Side-by-Side Comparison</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={mainComparisonColumns} rows={mainComparisonRows} />
  </div>

  <h2 id="safetywing">SafetyWing</h2>

  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-amber-100 text-amber-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Budget</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-amber-100 text-amber-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Monthly</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-amber-100 text-amber-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Emergency Only</span>
  </div>

  <p>
    SafetyWing is the cheapest option for long stays—$55/month with no commitment. But remember: it's travel medical insurance, not health insurance. Good for emergencies and accidents; limited for routine care, chronic conditions, or ongoing treatment.
  </p>

  <p><strong>Strengths:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Cheapest option ($55/month)</li>
    <li>Monthly subscription—no commitment</li>
    <li>No duration limits</li>
    <li>30 days home country coverage per 90 days</li>
    <li>Simple signup, instant coverage</li>
    <li>Good for emergencies abroad</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Weaknesses:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Travel medical, not health insurance</li>
    <li>$250K limit (low for serious illness)</li>
    <li>Limited routine care</li>
    <li>Pre-existing conditions not covered</li>
    <li>Mental health: crisis only</li>
    <li>May not meet visa requirements</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Young, healthy travelers on a budget. Those who just need emergency coverage. Gap year travelers. Snowbirds who are healthy.</p>

  <div class="my-6">
    <a href="/go/safetywing" class="inline-block bg-amber-600 hover:bg-amber-700 text-white font-medium py-2.5 px-5 rounded-lg transition-colors no-underline mr-3" style="color: white !important;">Get SafetyWing Quote</a>
    <a href="/providers/safetywing" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 font-medium">Read Full Review →</a>
  </div>

  <h2 id="allianz-care">Allianz Care</h2>

  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-green-100 text-green-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Real Insurance</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-green-100 text-green-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Full Coverage</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-green-100 text-green-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Pre-existing OK</span>
  </div>

  <p>
    Allianz Care provides actual health insurance—routine care, prescriptions, specialists, everything. More expensive than SafetyWing, but you get real coverage. Pre-existing conditions can be considered. Best for long stays where you need genuine healthcare access.
  </p>

  <p><strong>Strengths:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Real health insurance (not travel medical)</li>
    <li>Full routine and preventive care</li>
    <li>Pre-existing conditions underwritten</li>
    <li>€1M-3M coverage limits</li>
    <li>Best mental health coverage</li>
    <li>Meets visa requirements</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Weaknesses:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>3-4x more expensive than SafetyWing</li>
    <li>Annual commitment typically</li>
    <li>More paperwork to apply</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Serious long-stays (6+ months). Anyone with health conditions. Those who need routine care. Long-stay retirees and snowbirds.</p>

  <div class="my-6">
    <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block bg-green-600 hover:bg-green-700 text-white font-medium py-2.5 px-5 rounded-lg transition-colors no-underline mr-3" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    <a href="/providers/allianz-care" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 font-medium">Read Full Review →</a>
  </div>

  <h2 id="img-global">IMG Global</h2>

  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-neutral-200 text-neutral-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Middle Ground</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-neutral-200 text-neutral-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Flexible Terms</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-neutral-200 text-neutral-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Good Value</span>
  </div>

  <p>
    IMG Global bridges the gap between SafetyWing and premium insurers. Real health insurance at mid-range prices with flexible term options (6-24 months). Good for extended travel without full expat commitment.
  </p>

  <p><strong>Strengths:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Health insurance at moderate cost</li>
    <li>Flexible term lengths (6-24 months)</li>
    <li>Up to $8M coverage</li>
    <li>Pre-existing conditions considered</li>
    <li>Routine care included</li>
    <li>Good customer service</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Weaknesses:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>More expensive than SafetyWing</li>
    <li>Less comprehensive than Allianz</li>
    <li>Minimum term requirements</li>
    <li>Mental health coverage limited</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Extended travelers (6-24 months). Those who want real insurance without premium pricing. Gap year travelers with moderate health needs.</p>

  <div class="my-6">
    <a href="/go/img-global" class="inline-block bg-neutral-700 hover:bg-neutral-800 text-white font-medium py-2.5 px-5 rounded-lg transition-colors no-underline mr-3" style="color: white !important;">Get IMG Quote</a>
    <a href="/providers/img-global" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 font-medium">Read Full Review →</a>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Compare Long-Stay Options"
    description="Get quotes for your planned stay duration. Consider what coverage you actually need."
    buttonText="Get Free Quotes"
    buttonHref="/get-quotes"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="pricing">Pricing Comparison</h2>

  <p>
    The price spread is significant. SafetyWing costs roughly 1/3 of comprehensive options—but provides different (more limited) coverage.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={pricingColumns} rows={pricingRows} />
  </div>

  <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500">
    *Estimated costs excluding US coverage. SafetyWing prices for Nomad Insurance product.
  </p>

  <h2 id="long-stay-needs">What Long-Stay Travelers Need to Consider</h2>

  <h3>Travel Medical vs. Health Insurance</h3>
  <p>
    Critical distinction:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Travel medical (SafetyWing):</strong> Emergencies and accidents only. Not for routine care, ongoing conditions, or regular healthcare.</li>
    <li><strong>Health insurance (Allianz, IMG):</strong> Full coverage including routine visits, prescriptions, preventive care, specialists.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Pre-existing Conditions</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>SafetyWing:</strong> Not covered at all</li>
    <li><strong>IMG:</strong> May be covered after underwriting</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz:</strong> Most flexible—moratorium or underwriting options</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Visa Requirements</h3>
  <p>
    Some long-stay visas require health insurance (not travel medical):
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>SafetyWing may not meet requirements</li>
    <li>IMG and Allianz typically qualify</li>
    <li>Check your specific visa requirements</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Home Country Visits</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>SafetyWing:</strong> 30 days per 90-day period included</li>
    <li><strong>IMG:</strong> Optional add-on</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz:</strong> Optional add-on</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Snowbirds (Winter in Warm Climates)</h3>
  <p>
    If you spend 3-6 months abroad in winter:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Young and healthy: SafetyWing may suffice</li>
    <li>Over 50 or with conditions: Consider IMG or Allianz</li>
    <li>Make sure you have coverage when home too</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="best-for">Which Is Best For You?</h2>

  <div class="space-y-4 my-8">
    <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Choose SafetyWing if you...</h3>
      <ul class="text-neutral-600 space-y-1">
        <li>Are under 40 and healthy</li>
        <li>Just need emergency coverage</li>
        <li>Are on a tight budget</li>
        <li>Want month-to-month flexibility</li>
        <li>Don't have pre-existing conditions</li>
        <li>Your visa accepts travel insurance</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Choose Allianz Care if you...</h3>
      <ul class="text-neutral-600 space-y-1">
        <li>Need real health insurance</li>
        <li>Have pre-existing conditions</li>
        <li>Want routine care covered</li>
        <li>Are staying 6+ months</li>
        <li>Need to meet visa requirements</li>
        <li>Are over 50 or have health needs</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Choose IMG Global if you...</h3>
      <ul class="text-neutral-600 space-y-1">
        <li>Want middle-ground coverage and cost</li>
        <li>Have moderate health needs</li>
        <li>Prefer flexible term lengths</li>
        <li>Are doing a gap year</li>
        <li>Want real insurance without premium pricing</li>
        <li>Need coverage for 6-24 months</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <h3>How long is "long-stay"?</h3>
  <p>
    Generally 3+ months. Under 3 months, regular travel insurance often works. Over 12 months, you're essentially an expat and should consider full international health insurance. The 3-12 month range is where these options make most sense.
  </p>

  <h3>Can I extend SafetyWing indefinitely?</h3>
  <p>
    Yes—it's a subscription with no end date. But remember it's travel medical, not health insurance. For stays over 6-12 months, consider whether you need more comprehensive coverage, especially if you're aging or your health changes.
  </p>

  <h3>What if I develop a condition while on SafetyWing?</h3>
  <p>
    Acute conditions that develop are covered for initial treatment. But ongoing care for chronic conditions isn't covered. If you develop something requiring long-term care, you'd need to upgrade to real health insurance—and that condition would then be pre-existing.
  </p>

  <h3>Is 6 months too short for annual insurance?</h3>
  <p>
    You can buy annual insurance for a 6-month stay—it just costs more per month of actual coverage. IMG offers 6-month options specifically. Some people buy annual and cancel (with prorated refund) if plans change.
  </p>

  <h3>What about travel insurance for the flights?</h3>
  <p>
    These health-focused products don't cover trip cancellation, lost baggage, etc. If you want those benefits, consider adding a separate travel insurance policy for the trip portion, or use a credit card with travel benefits.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This comparison is for informational purposes only. Coverage terms vary. Verify your specific visa requirements and compare actual quotes before purchasing.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
